<div id="review_4022988423" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/4022988423" />
    <a title="George" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/10168276-george"><img alt="George" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1511867378p2/10168276.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/4022988423?book_show_action=true">Jun 01, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="George" class="user" itemprop="url" name="George" href="/user/show/10168276-george">George</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer4022988423" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer14223798210847299114">An interesting, thought provoking, overly long, historical fiction novel set in Florence, Italy, mostly in the 1490s. At this time there has been the expulsion of the Medici family, with the religious reformer Savonarola controlling the city. Romola, the devoted daughter of a blind scholar, marries the politically savvy Greek, Tito. Tito is an excellently developed villain, duplicitous in politics, love and family. Romola slowly learns about who the real Tito is.<br/><br/>It is an interesting, rewarding r</span>
  <span id="freeText14223798210847299114" style="display:none">An interesting, thought provoking, overly long, historical fiction novel set in Florence, Italy, mostly in the 1490s. At this time there has been the expulsion of the Medici family, with the religious reformer Savonarola controlling the city. Romola, the devoted daughter of a blind scholar, marries the politically savvy Greek, Tito. Tito is an excellently developed villain, duplicitous in politics, love and family. Romola slowly learns about who the real Tito is.<br /><br />It is an interesting, rewarding reading experience however the detailed descriptions of Florence and the politics of the 1490s will not be to some readers tastes.<br /><br />Readers who enjoy Eliot’s writing style will find this book a worthwhile read.<br /><br />This book was first published in 1863.</span>
  <a data-text-id="14223798210847299114" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
